Guns Law Website

This repository contains the Next.js frontend for the Guns Law website. The site is now built with the App Router, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS as a clean frontend foundation for later backend work.

Stack

- Next.js
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- App Router

Project Structure

```text
.
├── public/
│   └── images/              # Static assets used by Next.js
├── src/
│   ├── app/                 # App Router routes and global styles
│   ├── components/          # Reusable site sections and shared UI
│   ├── content/             # Page-specific copy and structured content
│   └── lib/
│       ├── metadata.ts      # Shared metadata helper
│       └── siteConfig.ts    # Reusable firm/contact/site configuration
├── package.json
└── README
```

Routes

- `/`
- `/about`
- `/contact`
- `/privacy`
- `/terms`

Content Management

All repeated firm data lives in `src/lib/siteConfig.ts`, including:

- Firm and attorney names
- Titles
- Phone and email
- Address details
- Navigation and legal footer links
- Shared consultation text and disclaimers

Page-specific content lives in `src/content/`.

Local Development

Install dependencies:

```bash
npm install
```

Start the development server:

```bash
npm run dev
```

Build for production:

```bash
npm run build
```

Design Notes

- The site keeps the existing law-firm visual direction while moving the styling into Tailwind.
- Reusable sections are componentized for future extension.
- No backend, database, auth, Supabase, API routes, or server actions are included in this phase.

